# Movie database



Movie listings live in `movieDatabase` at the top of `app/main.js`. This is the source of truth for which movies appear on the wheel.



## Listing format



- Standard: `"Title (Year)"` — e.g. `"Aliens (1986)"`

- Series/franchise: `"Franchise (Series)"` — e.g. `"Alien (Series)"`, `"Men in Black (Series)"`

- Use the exact string everywhere (metadata keys, watched list, keeper labels)



## Adding movies



1. Append to the correct category array — category key must match exactly, including emoji (e.g. `"CAGE STAGE 🐷"`)

2. Check for duplicates with `isDuplicateListing` logic — do not add the same listing twice

3. Run `npm run generate-metadata:ps` to refresh `app/generated/movie-metadata.js`

4. Do not hand-edit `app/generated/movie-metadata.js`



The in-app Add Movies UI generates a prompt via `buildAddMoviesPrompt` (~line 2675) with the same instructions.



## Removing movies



When the user marks keeper picks as watched via Ticket Stubs, the app generates a remove prompt listing exact strings to delete from `movieDatabase`.



1. Find the exact listing string in the named category array (including year)

2. Remove only that entry — do not reformat surrounding listings

3. Regenerate metadata if the listing had OMDb data: `npm run generate-metadata:ps`



## Category sync



If adding a new category, also update:



- `scripts/win-clip-categories.mjs` — maps category name to `audio/win/<folder>/`

- Create the matching folder under `audio/win/` and run `npm run refresh-audio`

- `docs/CATEGORIES.md` — add a blurb entry for the new wheel



Category names must match across all locations. Category blurbs and grouping logic live in `docs/CATEGORIES.md` (when choosing which wheel a title belongs on).
